other_tests.findings: The appendix is diffusely enlarged, measuring 11 mm, and fluid filled with enhancement of the wall, and adjacent fat stranding. No periappendiceal abscess or evidence of perforation is noted. There are few prominent lymph nodes in the right lower abdomen. Small and large bowel appear unremarkable with no evidence of bowel obstruction. There is a small amount of mildly complex free fluid in the pelvis.
